[normal]If we consider the accident metric of fatality 
[normal]per millions of
[normal] cycle trips then the data is presented in the form of 
[normal]a s
[normal]catter Graph using Microsoft excel for the ten observation periods.  The accident metric has never fallen below 2.04 deaths per million of cycle trips during the 
[normal]past 
[normal]ten observation 
[normal]periods (See Figure2).   
[normal]Moreover the inspection of the graph shows that there is no co-relation between the average cycle trips per day and the resulting fatalities. 
[normal]&#xa0;
[normal]The figure of 2.04 deaths per million of cycle trips can be regarded as a subjective me
[normal]asure of mortality risk as per Paul Slovic‘s psychological criteria
[normal] 
[normal](Kahneman, 2011)
[normal]. However, the figure compared against a scientific criterion of chances of death per million, it is clear that the human activit
[normal]y of cycling i
[normal]n London
[normal] has become dangerous.
