[normal]The risk 
[normal]assessment 
[normal]criterion of one chance per million opportunities is
[normal] derived from Ian Murphy’s 1997 publication
[normal] 
[normal](Murphy, 1997)
[normal]. 
[normal]Apart from one outlier 
[normal](2008) 
[normal]during the observational 
[normal]period where the metric went down to 8 fatalities, the fatalities have been consistently in the double figure range. 
[normal]Further
[normal], statistics perspective of fatalities calculated are mean=15.6, median = 15.5, mode is 19 and standard deviation is 4.32. From these figures, using a Poisson probability distribution, the probability of first fatality is less than .04%. 
[normal] Author is of the 
[normal]opinion that cautious behaviour on part of the cyclists and road drivers shows up as a constraint upon the accident fatalities in accordance with Dr Ashby’s perspective
[normal] 
[normal](Ashby, 1957)
[normal]. 
