[normal]However, the text 
[normal]in this section shows that 
[normal]research into behavioural attitudes of cyclists as suggested by Transport for London document is 
[normal]not useful 
[normal]activity
[normal]. Let us consider the fact that 
[normal]in 2009 there were 13 fatalities 
[normal]and 33
[normal]96 injuries (see Chapter 2 London Transport document).  
[normal]From t
[normal]hese figures 
[normal]it can be inferred that
[normal] there were 3409 collision events
[normal] between a cyclist and other vehicle
[normal] in the following manner
